{
  "texts": [
    "It includes 7,665 English self-reported events from around 3,000 respondents from 37 countries across five continents.",
    "The respondents were asked to report situations in which they had experienced seven major emotions (ANGER, DISGUST, FEAR, GUILT, JOY, SADNESS, and SHAME) which encompass the six emotions proposed by Ekman (1992), excluding SURPRISE.",
    "This dataset contains demographic information for each respondent, including (binary) gender, religion, and country of origin.",
    "We use the gender for conducting the experiments shown in Section 5.1.",
    "We removed any instances with invalid events like \"NO RESPONSE\"."
  ]
}